			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Good day fellow mages.
<br />

<br />
In some long ago patch the spell root was made so that the closest player character to the monster rooted would take the agro, no matter what the status of the hate list at the time.
<br />

<br />
Because of this effect, our earth pet (and to a limited extent, our fire pet) is not a welcome member in groups.  This is frustrating to me, because often times an add will start chasing a healer and I don't have the option of rooting that add while everything gets under control, and have to hope that the air pet lands a stun and gets some agro in order to "save the day".
<br />

<br />
My question is, why is this necessary? What about this makes sense and why can root not be made more group friendly all around? 
<br />

<br />
My theory is that due to limitations in the agro code, if a creature is rooted he cannot attack who is highest on his hate list, and if that creature cannot summon he would stand there staring angrily at his most hated foe but otherwise unacting until root broke.  The way to stop that of course would be to change the agro code so that a rooted creature just attacks whoever is closest to them.
<br />

<br />
If root could be changed to make a creature agro whoever is highest on the hate list AND in melee range of the mob then root would be group friendly and we could use earth pets in groups with no worries.
<br />

<br />
I'm tired of accepting this "because that's the way it is" when it makes no sense.  We should be asking SoE to fix this, as it would give us root in groups and a form of crowd control.<br />_________________<br />Kimberly Shaw
<br />
Erudite Debutante Mistress Arch Convoker 
<br />
I wish I was like you, Easily amused
<br />
Choking on the ashes of her enemy
<br />
