				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The problem with the tank moving closer to the mob to get aggro when a mob is rooted is what generally ends up happening is the other melees crowd in jocking for position if you have more then 3 melees. Usually the rogue trying to keep rear position for BS. Then either they get too close and get aggro OR the tank has to get so close he overlaps and cannot even hit the mob. At which point he steps back losing aggro to those crowding in. Root is really a horrible spell to cast on a mob if it is being tanked.<br />_________________<br />Hilbur Helpmate
<br />
Archon of Brell
<br />
Unspoken Legacy</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
